Virginia Tech, a serene university in Blacksburg, Virginia, was rocked by a tragic shooting that claimed 32 lives.
The campus, nestled in the Blue Ridge mountains, is the heart of the town of Blacksburg.
The university's $900 million budget drives the local economy.
Founded in 1872, Virginia Tech was a land-grant school focused on practical education.
The shooting, the deadliest in US history, left the nation in shock.
President Bush attended a memorial service to honor the victims.
The campus community was urged to stay vigilant as authorities investigated the tragedy.
